Then you can inject this class into your service class. Now if you want to run it concurrency. You could try `@Async` and `Future` [here](https://www.baeldung.com/spring-async#the-async-annotation). Just need a little bit of change on the new service and remember to call Future.get() on your main service.

```java
@Async
public Future&lt;CustomerInfo&gt; getCustomerInfo() {
